Samuel D. COLLINS, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 12932. United States Court of Appeals Ninth Circuit. Nov. 9, 1951. Samuel D. Collins, in pro per. Ernest A. Tolin, U. S. Atty., Ray H. Kinnison and Bernard B. Laven, Assts. U. S. Atty., all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before MATHEWS, STEPHENS and ORR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order appealed from is affirmed.
